1
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:30,839
We can grow two seasons of grain a year in Hainan

2
00:00:31,199 --> 00:00:33,119
But mostly we grow tropical fruit trees

3
00:00:33,399 --> 00:00:35,640
It's basically traditional farming

4
00:00:35,759 --> 00:00:37,159
The level of mechanization isn't high

5
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:39,200
Because of the tropical climate

6
00:00:39,399 --> 00:00:40,280
There's a lot of rainfall

7
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:42,920
So preventing mold and rot is also quite important

8
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:46,600
What did I do to deserve this?

9
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,039
Why does the department have to go to Hainan?

10
00:00:48,039 --> 00:00:49,520
To work on experimental planting fields?

11
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:50,520
Can I not go?

12
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,640
I don't want to go back to Hainan

13
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:53,159
I want to go on a vacation

14
00:00:53,159 --> 00:00:53,640
Xiaoyin

15
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:56,399
Darn it

16
00:01:00,119 --> 00:01:02,399
Xiaoyin, for this field trip, I'd like to

17
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:03,719
assign you to lead the team

18
00:01:03,719 --> 00:01:05,000
See if that works for you

19
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,200
It works

20
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:09,040
That's great

21
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:10,400
I feel much more at ease with you there

22
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,519
Thank you, Xiaoyin

23
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:16,040
The trees for this experimental planting

24
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:17,200
have already been planted at the base

25
00:01:17,359 --> 00:01:19,319
and professionals are responsible for their cultivation

26
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:20,280
As for the new tree species

27
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,840
mainly in terms of pest control

28
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,280
some upgrades and modifications were made

29
00:01:23,599 --> 00:01:25,959
so we need to collect a large amount of field data

30
00:01:26,519 --> 00:01:28,799
Professor, so for the data collection this time

31
00:01:28,799 --> 00:01:31,000
will we use the lab's latest equipment

32
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,400
to go "Dudu"?

33
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,519
We won't be going "Dudu" this time

34
00:01:37,359 --> 00:01:39,439
The main task for undergraduate students this time

35
00:01:40,439 --> 00:01:41,439
is counting bugs

36
00:01:43,319 --> 00:01:44,760
Guifang, I'm scared of bugs

37
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,359
I can't do it, bugs are what I fear most

38
00:01:46,359 --> 00:01:47,799
I really don't want to go count bugs

39
00:01:48,959 --> 00:01:49,640
However

40
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:52,879
is the holiday internship linked to the postgraduate recommendation?

41
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:58,359
The number of bugs is one data point

42
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:00,680
Of course, there are other data to record

43
00:02:00,959 --> 00:02:03,280
This is a very rare opportunity for practice

44
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,519
Although it's very hard work

45
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,599
and quite boring

46
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:06,799
I still hope

47
00:02:06,799 --> 00:02:08,800
students will sign up enthusiastically

48
00:02:09,319 --> 00:02:09,840
I'll sign up

49
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:11,000
Good

50
00:02:11,919 --> 00:02:13,439
Guifang, you're the best

51
00:02:13,439 --> 00:02:14,639
You're going to keep me company, right?

52
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:17,120
Professor Wang

53
00:02:17,319 --> 00:02:18,840
Do we have that insect atlas?

54
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:20,800
So how should we classify these bugs?

55
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,680
Besides counting, do we have to kill them?

56
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:23,479
What date are we leaving?

57
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,000
I'll answer you later

58
00:02:26,919 --> 00:02:29,520
I've left the sign-up sheet with team leader Chen Xiaoyin

59
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:31,120
Students who want to go can sign up with her

60
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:32,520
You don't need to rush

61
00:02:32,599 --> 00:02:33,879
Think it over for the next couple of days

62
00:02:33,879 --> 00:02:34,560
Consider it carefully

63
00:02:35,199 --> 00:02:35,639
Class dismissed

64
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:44,120
As expected of Kong Guifang, who took the college by storm

65
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,000
Thanks to her

66
00:02:45,319 --> 00:02:46,599
I'm still carrying a disciplinary record

67
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:48,680
Suddenly I don't know if I should be afraid of Guifang

68
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,000
or afraid of the bugs

69
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:54,719
Does anyone else want to sign up?

70
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:23,919
Xiaocan

71
00:03:24,439 --> 00:03:25,960
Come with us to Hainan later

72
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:33,840
Why wear a hat and sunglasses at home?

73
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:01,680
So your mom became like this

74
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:02,520
all because of you, right?

75
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,120
You... listen to me.

76
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:04,759
I heard everything.

77
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:05,599
What else is there to say?

78
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:08,120
You've instantly turned into a boiled egg.

79
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,120
And you're still making things up.

80
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,479
It's... it's a bit complicated.

81
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:12,719
So you're dying, aren't you?

82
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,680
It's possible, but...

83
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,839
Was that an alien just now?

84
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:18,600
Yes.

85
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:19,480
Call him back.

86
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,519
I'm telling you, the consequences are serious.

87
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:24,079
It's you, isn't it?

88
00:04:25,279 --> 00:04:26,360
You made him like this, right?

89
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,199
Change him back right now.

90
00:04:28,199 --> 00:04:29,120
It's my job.

91
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,120
What kind of bullshit job is that?

92
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,480
Does a job give you the right to disregard life?

93
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:32,439
Are you even human?

94
00:04:32,519 --> 00:04:33,680
Well, I'm not human to begin with.

95
00:04:33,839 --> 00:04:34,639
Change him back immediately.

96
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:35,480
Hurry up!

97
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:37,199
Xu... Xu Rui.

98
00:04:37,199 --> 00:04:38,319
Don't... don't be rash. Um...

99
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:40,920
Where is he?

100
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,120
He has a teleportation power.

101
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,279
I can't control him either.

102
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:45,279
But you were right to scold him just now.

103
00:04:45,279 --> 00:04:46,160
And you, Kong Xiaocan.

104
00:04:46,399 --> 00:04:47,519
You think treating your life like a joke

105
00:04:47,519 --> 00:04:48,360
makes you noble, huh?

106
00:04:48,439 --> 00:04:50,000
No, call him back right now. Quick!

107
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:51,839
No, it's useless if I call him.

108
00:04:51,839 --> 00:04:53,000
He's never listened to me.

109
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:54,439
She knows too much.

110
00:04:54,519 --> 00:04:55,000
I must...

111
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:55,639
You...

112
00:04:57,959 --> 00:04:59,879
See? I told you you can't catch him.

113
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,519
Kong Xiaocan!

114
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,360
Don't ask me again.

115
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,399
I really can't catch him.

116
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,160
I'll erase her memory.

117
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:06,399
Quick!

118
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,240
You run pretty fast.

119
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:20,360
Yeah.

120
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,120
This time, it's this way.

121
00:05:23,959 --> 00:05:26,319
Xu Rui, actually, about this...

122
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,079
I did it willingly.

123
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:30,160
I did make a trade to save my mom's life.

124
00:05:30,759 --> 00:05:31,879
Although the price is high...

125
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,199
but look at my mom now.

126
00:05:33,519 --> 00:05:34,279
She really is...

127
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,519
Run! My hair, my hair!

128
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,639
Keep running!

129
00:05:40,639 --> 00:05:41,519
I won't run, I won't run! You're pretty fast.

130
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,199
Change him back right now. Quick!

131
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:45,720
I can't change him back.

132
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:47,399
Because I made a deal with him.

133
00:05:47,519 --> 00:05:48,639
If you keep interfering...

134
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:50,160
things will get even more chaotic.

135
00:05:50,319 --> 00:05:50,839
What do you mean?

136
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,040
It means that...

137
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,040
an outsider like you who hasn't made a deal...

138
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:58,240
could put him in even greater danger.

139
00:05:59,399 --> 00:06:00,399
Yes, that's right.

140
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:03,639
Then I'll make the trade.

141
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,480
Rui, don't be impulsive.

142
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,680
He's a profiteer.

143
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:20,879
Don't worry.

144
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,120
I know what I'm doing.

145
00:06:23,399 --> 00:06:24,399
Sorry to keep you waiting.

146
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,319
Based on your life experience,

147
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,720
here is a customized deal for you.

148
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,519
Please take a look.

149
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,560
Simple.

150
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:30,839
Clear.

151
00:06:31,399 --> 00:06:31,800
Efficient.

152
00:06:33,079 --> 00:06:33,560
Here is another one.

153
00:06:35,399 --> 00:06:36,560
But having said that,

154
00:06:37,079 --> 00:06:39,399
I usually customize requests for clients.

155
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:42,600
I didn't expect someone to seek me out for a deal.

156
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:43,959
This is a first.

157
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:45,800
Come, let me introduce this to you.

158
00:06:46,519 --> 00:06:47,199
Like this one.

159
00:06:47,319 --> 00:06:50,240
This is the Permanent Dark Circle Removal Package.

160
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:53,399
No matter how late you stay up, no dark circles.

161
00:06:53,399 --> 00:06:55,639
Giving you back beautiful big eyes.

162
00:06:56,439 --> 00:06:57,720
It only costs eight years of lifespan now.

163
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,920
What exactly is this life energy?

164
00:07:03,319 --> 00:07:04,319
Why do you want it?

165
00:07:05,879 --> 00:07:07,480
What is life energy?

166
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:08,839
Good question.

167
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:11,279
Life energy is like gasoline.

168
00:07:12,399 --> 00:07:13,959
A car only runs when you add gas.

169
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,759
Only then can it drive normally.

170
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,160
The difference is,

171
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,160
you lifeforms on Earth

172
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:24,000
can replenish energy through photosynthesis

173
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,720
or by eating food.

174
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,399
But we cannot.

175
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:34,959
We can only

176
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:37,639
extract a portion of energy from you.

177
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,120
Just like this.

178
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,879
However, it's hard for you to get energy too.

179
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:50,519
So,

180
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,399
we provide some benefits

181
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,160
as compensation.

182
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:54,680
Like curing diseases, becoming beautiful or handsome,

183
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:55,839
changing your appearance, and so on.

184
00:07:57,279 --> 00:07:58,560
Isn't that just robbery?

185
00:07:59,839 --> 00:08:00,439
It's not robbery.

186
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,560
We can't just extract energy whenever we want.

187
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:04,680
You have to go through complex approval processes.

188
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,160
Uploading, approving...

189
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,120
Approval? Who approves it?

190
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,959
The company supervisors.

191
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,120
We also follow rules and procedures.

192
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,519
The word "company,"

193
00:08:12,519 --> 00:08:14,040
we actually learned it from you humans.

194
00:08:14,199 --> 00:08:14,959
Very efficient.

195
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,759
Let me introduce another one.

196
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:18,720
The Eat-Without-Gaining-Weight Package.

197
00:08:18,879 --> 00:08:20,279
You won't gain weight no matter how much you eat.

198
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:21,680
It only costs twenty years of lifespan.

199
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,680
Twenty years?

200
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:26,680
Do you know the average human lifespan?

201
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,480
You ask for twenty years right off the bat?

202
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,160
Are you crazy?

203
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,040
There are cheaper ones.

204
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:31,279
Curing your ankle is very cheap.

205
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,159
Only six years.

206
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:34,799
Restore Xiaocan and Auntie Kong to normal.

207
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,480
Cancel the deal. How many years?

208
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:39,480
Dear, I'm afraid that's not possible.

209
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:42,399
Putting aside that we have no return or refund policy,

210
00:08:42,639 --> 00:08:43,320
even if we did,

211
00:08:43,639 --> 00:08:44,639
she has cancer.

212
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,679
To cure her completely

213
00:08:46,679 --> 00:08:47,840
and let her live a healthy life,

214
00:08:48,039 --> 00:08:50,240
might require hundreds of years of life energy.

215
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,600
Humans cannot afford this price.

216
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,759
Won't you really consider these plans?

217
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:58,960
I'm not interested.

218
00:08:59,879 --> 00:09:01,200
Give me time to think it over.

219
00:09:01,679 --> 00:09:02,440
I'll tell you when I've decided.

220
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,080
Do you have a phone number?

221
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,080
No.

222
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,600
How can I contact you without a phone?

223
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,759
Don't tell me you'll come if I snap my fingers?

224
00:09:10,039 --> 00:09:10,360
Yes.

225
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,200
As long as you snap your fingers,

226
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:14,360
I'll be there anytime.

227
00:09:16,799 --> 00:09:17,600
Do you want to look again?

228
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:18,879
Leave now.

229
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,600
Looking forward to our next collaboration.

230
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,120
You made up your mind so fast?

231
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,120
I'll just give it a try.

232
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:41,759
Then next time...

233
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,120
Say,

234
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,360
when we get to Hainan,

235
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,000
will we have unlimited fruit?

236
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,440
Not really.

237
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,679
Even apples are rare in Hainan.

238
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,480
It's mostly mangoes and coconuts.

239
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,360
You'll get sick of them in two days.

240
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,039
Xiaoyin, look.

241
00:10:00,799 --> 00:10:01,480
Which one looks better?

242
00:10:03,399 --> 00:10:05,000
They both look good. Take them both.

243
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:05,679
I think so too.

244
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:06,919
I think these two...

245
00:10:06,919 --> 00:10:08,320
go really well with the sea.

246
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,279
But, the color of the sea...

247
00:10:10,279 --> 00:10:12,559
mainly depends on the weather at the time.

248
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:13,639
I checked the weather forecast.

249
00:10:13,639 --> 00:10:15,480
It says it might rain the two days we're there.

250
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:16,559
Rain is great!

251
00:10:16,559 --> 00:10:17,279
If it rains,

252
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,279
our saplings can drink their fill.

253
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,279
Fang'er, why do you like Hainan so much?

254
00:10:23,519 --> 00:10:24,879
Don't you like your hometown?

255
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:27,600
Forget it.

256
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,120
Professor Wang asked me to book tickets.

257
00:10:30,519 --> 00:10:31,320
I was thinking,

258
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,639
we students should save the school some money.

259
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,320
So I'll book hard sleepers on the train.

260
00:10:35,759 --> 00:10:37,600
It's 944 per person for a round trip.

261
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,159
I'm going to book it. Hanging up now.

262
00:10:39,519 --> 00:10:39,960
Wait a minute.

263
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,000
Can we bring a few people at their own expense?

264
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:45,679
I want to invite Xiaocan and the others.

265
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,000
Just treat it as a vacation.

266
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,240
Then when there's nothing to do,

267
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,799
they can help us count bugs.

268
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,879
Sure, let them come.

269
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:52,679
We can hang out together.

270
00:10:53,279 --> 00:10:54,000
Actually,

271
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:55,480
otherwise I'd be farming every day,

272
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,600
and having to face my mom.

273
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,759
You don't need to worry about accommodation.

274
00:10:58,759 --> 00:10:59,799
Stay at my place. My house is big.

275
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,279
Then I won't be polite.

276
00:11:01,279 --> 00:11:01,799
No problem, no problem.

277
00:11:01,799 --> 00:11:03,159
Send me the ticket information.

278
00:11:03,279 --> 00:11:04,399
I'll have Xiaocan and the others book the same one.

279
00:11:04,399 --> 00:11:05,519
Okay, I'll send it to you in a bit.

280
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:06,919
Hanging up. Bye-bye.

281
00:11:07,559 --> 00:11:08,200
Xiaocan.

282
00:11:08,759 --> 00:11:11,279
Go tell Xu Rui, Li Wai, and the others,

283
00:11:11,399 --> 00:11:12,519
